SampleDescription.Description: 3 cell lines: 46,XX,-13,+r; 46,XX,+13,der(13;13)(q10;q10); 46,XX,+13,der(13;13)(q10;q10)del(13)(q12.1q14.1). Phenotype: dysmorphic features, low set ears, sacral dimple, floppy airway, broad nasal bridge, natal teeth present, digitalized thumbs, overlapped toes, possible MRI abnormalities. Mom has had three miscarriages.

ClinicalAssertion.StudyDescription: Copy number variation identified through the course of routine clinical cytogenomic testing in postnatal populations, with clinical assertions as classified by the original submitter.
